results.name: Triangle read by rows: row n gives the first arithmetic progression of n primes with minimal distance, cf. A033188.
comment: The first 10 rows (i.e., 55 terms) are the same as for A133277 (where the final term is minimal), but here a(56) = T(11,1) = 608581797 while A133277(11,1) = 110437. - _M. F. Hasler_, Jan 02 2020
link: Index entries for sequences related to primes in arithmetic progressions
example: Row 10 is the same as in A086786, A113470, A133277, and listed as A033168. - _M. F. Hasler_, Jan 02 2020
xref: For common differences see A033188, for initial terms see A033189.
Different from A133277 (from T(11,1) = a(56) on).
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Oct 17 2007
